article.headline: Wichita St. 75, Cal St.-Fullerton 60
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Carl Hall had 19 points and eight rebounds to lead Wichita State to a 75-60 victory over Cal State-Fullerton on Thursday night. Joe Ragland added 15 points and David Kyles contributed 14 points and seven rebounds for the Shockers (4-2), who held a 37-27 rebounding edge in the game. Toure Murry had seven assists for Wichita State. Omondi Amoke led the Titans (3-3) with 19 points. Kwame Vaughn added 11 and D.J. Seeley had 10 points and a team-high five rebounds. The Shockers host No. 18 UNLV (8-0) on Sunday as part of the Mountain West-Missouri Valley Challenge.
